      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It makes sense that self-care feels hollow when the scale of destruction is so overwhelming, like mourning grief while a storm rage threatens to destroy the world. Instead of forcing denial, try confronting the despair to release it openly into grief or anger, rather than burying it under forced hope. This painful grieving can eventually carve out space for grief to eventually burn into hope, even if that flame burns very low to start with.",
